1. KalobaNaso Spray Arm: This arm will recruit participants who will receive the KalobaNaso spray (2 puffs per nostril, 3 times a day) as part of the intervention. To be eligible for this arm, participants must meet the following criteria:

- 18 years of age or older (or legal representative if participant is a child);
- Diagnosed with common cold, nasal mucosal inflammation, or rhinitis;
- Provide informed consent (or parent/caregiver for children under 18 years old);
- Able to administer KalobaNaso spray properly.

2. Active Comparator Arm: This arm will recruit participants who will receive a licensed nasal decongestant (active comparator) spray (as per manufacturer recommendations) as part of the intervention. To be eligible for this arm, participants must meet the following criteria:

- 18 years of age or older (or legal representative if participant is a child);
- Diagnosed with common cold, nasal mucosal inflammation, or rhinitis;
- Provide informed consent (or parent/caregiver for children under 18 years old);
- Able to administer the active comparator spray properly.

For children under 18 years old in the Active Comparator Arm, the active comparator spray is adjusted according to their age and weight as recommended by the manufacturer.

Feel free to let me know if you have any questions or concerns regarding the study arms.
